  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Milk Production and Local Development in Ayabaca-IGCH</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will work with small-farming communities in Cujaca and San Bartolome de Olleros, which are located in the Ayabaca Province in the Piura Region. The greatest problems these communties face are poverty manifested particularly in food insecurity, poor management of their natural resources and lack of capacity for community management and for working with venues of public participation in order for their demands for better living conditions be ehard and attended to.  The project will support the communities&apos; response to the situation of poverty by improving their handling of their production resources, food security and milk production; contributing to improve their production and food systems; promoting community strengthening for improved advocacy with regard to plans for local development and real participation for inclusive and sustainable development. Five hundred thirty (530) families (265 original and 265 pass-on) will participate in the project. The project will provide cows, guinea pigs, seeds, irrigation systems and agroecological activities and will include the linking of local knowledge to all project activities as well as providing support to a more organized and effective participation in local markets`</narrative>
  </description>
